A farmer got so old that he couldn&rsquo;t work the fields anymore. So he would spend the day just sitting on the porch. His son, still working the farm, would look up from time to time and see his father sitting there.
&ldquo;He&rsquo;s of no use any more,&rdquo; the son thought to himself, &ldquo;he doesn&rsquo;t do anything!&ldquo;
One day the son got so frustrated by this, that he built a wood coffin, dragged it over to the porch, and told his father to get in.
